157 #if !defined(ELPP_DISABLE_ASSERT)
158 #if (defined(ELPP_DEBUG_ASSERT_FAILURE))
159 #define ELPP_ASSERT(expr, msg) \
160  if (!(expr)) \
161  { \
162  std::stringstream internalInfoStream; \
163  internalInfoStream << msg; \
164  ELPP_INTERNAL_DEBUGGING_OUT_ERROR << "EASYLOGGING++ ASSERTION FAILED (LINE: " << __LINE__ << ") [" #expr \
165  << "] WITH MESSAGE \"" \
166  << ELPP_INTERNAL_DEBUGGING_MSG(internalInfoStream.str()) << "\"" \
167  << ELPP_INTERNAL_DEBUGGING_ENDL; \
168  base::utils::abort(1, "ELPP Assertion failure, please define ELPP_DEBUG_ASSERT_FAILURE"); \
169  }
170 #else
171 #define ELPP_ASSERT(expr, msg) \
172  if (!(expr)) \
173  { \
174  std::stringstream internalInfoStream; \
175  internalInfoStream << msg; \
176  ELPP_INTERNAL_DEBUGGING_OUT_ERROR << "ASSERTION FAILURE FROM EASYLOGGING++ (LINE: " << __LINE__ << ") [" #expr \
177  << "] WITH MESSAGE \"" \
178  << ELPP_INTERNAL_DEBUGGING_MSG(internalInfoStream.str()) << "\"" \
179  << ELPP_INTERNAL_DEBUGGING_ENDL; \
180  }
181 #endif // (defined(ELPP_DEBUG_ASSERT_FAILURE))
182 #else
183 #define ELPP_ASSERT(x, y)
184 #endif //(!defined(ELPP_DISABLE_ASSERT)

186 #define ELPP_INTERNAL_DEBUGGING_WRITE_PERROR \
187  { \
188  char buff[256]; \
189  strerror_s(buff, 256, errno); \
190  ELPP_INTERNAL_DEBUGGING_OUT_ERROR << ": " << buff << " [" << errno << "]"; \
191  } \
192  (void)0

202  std::stringstream internalInfoStream; \
203  internalInfoStream << "<ERROR> " << msg; \
204  ELPP_INTERNAL_DEBUGGING_OUT_ERROR << "ERROR FROM EASYLOGGING++ (LINE: " << __LINE__ << ") " \

955 class Mutex : base::NoCopy
956 {
957 public:
958  Mutex(void)
959  {
960 #if ELPP_OS_UNIX
961  pthread_mutexattr_t attr;
962  pthread_mutexattr_init(&attr);
963  pthread_mutexattr_settype(&attr, PTHREAD_MUTEX_RECURSIVE);
964  pthread_mutex_init(&m_underlyingMutex, &attr);
965  pthread_mutexattr_destroy(&attr);
966 #elif ELPP_OS_WINDOWS
967  InitializeCriticalSection(&m_underlyingMutex);
968 #endif // ELPP_OS_UNIX
969  }
970 
971  virtual ~Mutex(void)
972  {
973 #if ELPP_OS_UNIX
974  pthread_mutex_destroy(&m_underlyingMutex);
975 #elif ELPP_OS_WINDOWS
976  DeleteCriticalSection(&m_underlyingMutex);
977 #endif // ELPP_OS_UNIX
978  }
979 
980  inline void lock(void)
981  {
982 #if ELPP_OS_UNIX
983  pthread_mutex_lock(&m_underlyingMutex);
984 #elif ELPP_OS_WINDOWS
985  EnterCriticalSection(&m_underlyingMutex);
986 #endif // ELPP_OS_UNIX
987  }
988 
989  inline bool try_lock(void)
990  {
991 #if ELPP_OS_UNIX
992  return (pthread_mutex_trylock(&m_underlyingMutex) == 0);
993 #elif ELPP_OS_WINDOWS
994  return TryEnterCriticalSection(&m_underlyingMutex);
995 #endif // ELPP_OS_UNIX
996  }
997 
998  inline void unlock(void)
999  {
1000 #if ELPP_OS_UNIX
1001  pthread_mutex_unlock(&m_underlyingMutex);
1002 #elif ELPP_OS_WINDOWS
1003  LeaveCriticalSection(&m_underlyingMutex);
1004 #endif // ELPP_OS_UNIX
1005  }
1006 
1007 private:
1008 #if ELPP_OS_UNIX
1009  pthread_mutex_t m_underlyingMutex;
1010 #elif ELPP_OS_WINDOWS
1011  CRITICAL_SECTION m_underlyingMutex;
1012 #endif // ELPP_OS_UNIX
1013 };

1366 template <typename T_Ptr, typename Container> class AbstractRegistry : public base::threading::ThreadSafe
1367 {
1368 public:
1369  typedef typename Container::iterator iterator;
1370  typedef typename Container::const_iterator const_iterator;
1371 
1373  AbstractRegistry(void)
1374  {
1375  }
1376 
1378  AbstractRegistry(AbstractRegistry&& sr)
1379  {
1380  if (this == &sr)
1381  {
1382  return;
1383  }
1384  unregisterAll();
1385  m_list = std::move(sr.m_list);
1386  }
1387 
1388  bool operator==(const AbstractRegistry<T_Ptr, Container>& other)
1389  {
1390  if (size() != other.size())
1391  {
1392  return false;
1393  }
1394  for (std::size_t i = 0; i < m_list.size(); ++i)
1395  {
1396  if (m_list.at(i) != other.m_list.at(i))
1397  {
1398  return false;
1399  }
1400  }
1401  return true;
1402  }
1403 
1404  bool operator!=(const AbstractRegistry<T_Ptr, Container>& other)
1405  {
1406  if (size() != other.size())
1407  {
1408  return true;
1409  }
1410  for (std::size_t i = 0; i < m_list.size(); ++i)
1411  {
1412  if (m_list.at(i) != other.m_list.at(i))
1413  {
1414  return true;
1415  }
1416  }
1417  return false;
1418  }
1419 
1421  AbstractRegistry& operator=(AbstractRegistry&& sr)
1422  {
1423  if (this == &sr)
1424  {
1425  return *this;
1426  }
1427  unregisterAll();
1428  m_list = std::move(sr.m_list);
1429  return *this;
1430  }
1431 
1432  virtual ~AbstractRegistry(void)
1433  {
1434  }
1435 
1437  virtual inline iterator begin(void) ELPP_FINAL
1438  {
1439  return m_list.begin();
1440  }
1441

1522  }
1523  this->reinitDeepCopy(sr);

1534  }

1536  return *this;

1544 protected:

1546  {

1550  {
1551  base::utils::safeDelete(curr.second);
1552  }
1553  this->list().clear();
1554  }
1555  }
1556 
1558  virtual void registerNew(const T_Key& uniqKey, T_Ptr* ptr) ELPP_FINAL

1561  this->list().insert(std::make_pair(uniqKey, ptr));

1571  base::utils::safeDelete(existing);
1572  }
1573  }
1574 
1576  T_Ptr* get(const T_Key& uniqKey)
1577  {

1579  return it == this->list().end() ? nullptr : it->second;
1580  }

1584  {

1586  {
1587  registerNew(it->first, new T_Ptr(*it->second));
1588  }

2239  bool includeGlobalLevel = true)
2240  {
2241  // If map is empty and we are allowed to add into generic level (Level::Global), do it!
2242  if (confMap->empty() && includeGlobalLevel)
2243  {
2244  confMap->insert(std::make_pair(Level::Global, value));
2245  return;
2246  }
2247  // If same value exist in generic level already, dont add it to explicit level
2248  typename std::unordered_map<Level, Conf_T>::iterator it = confMap->find(Level::Global);
2249  if (it != confMap->end() && it->second == value)
2250  {
2251  return;
2252  }
2253  // Now make sure we dont double up values if we really need to add it to explicit level
2254  it = confMap->find(level);
2255  if (it == confMap->end())
2256  {
2257  // Value not found for level, add new
2258  confMap->insert(std::make_pair(level, value));
2259  }
2260  else
2261  {
2262  // Value found, just update value
2263  confMap->at(level) = value;
2264  }

3704 template <typename T, typename... Args>
3705 void Logger::log_(Level level, int vlevel, const char* s, const T& value, const Args&... args)
3706 {
3707  base::MessageBuilder b;
3708  b.initialize(this);
3709  while (*s)
3710  {
3711  if (*s == base::consts::kFormatSpecifierChar)
3712  {
3713  if (*(s + 1) == base::consts::kFormatSpecifierChar)
3714  {
3715  ++s;
3716  }
3717  else
3718  {
3719  if (*(s + 1) == base::consts::kFormatSpecifierCharValue)
3720  {
3721  ++s;
3722  b << value;
3723  log_(level, vlevel, ++s, args...);
3724  return;
3725  }
3726  }
3727  }
3728  b << *s++;
3729  }
3730  ELPP_INTERNAL_ERROR("Too many arguments provided. Unable to handle. Please provide more format specifiers", false);
3731 }
3732 template <typename T> void Logger::log_(Level level, int vlevel, const T& _log)
3733 {
3734  if (level == Level::Verbose)
3735  {
3736  if (ELPP->vRegistry()->allowed(vlevel, __FILE__))
3737  {
3738  base::Writer(Level::Verbose, "FILE", 0, "FUNCTION", base::DispatchAction::NormalLog, vlevel)
3739  .construct(this, false)
3740  << _log;
3741  }
3742  else
3743  {
3744  stream().str(ELPP_LITERAL(""));
3745  releaseLock();
3746  }
3747  }
3748  else
3749  {
3750  base::Writer(level, "FILE", 0, "FUNCTION").construct(this, false) << _log;
3751  }
3752 }

3755 {
3756  acquireLock(); // released in Writer!
3757  log_(level, 0, s, value, args...);
3758 }

3760 {
3761  acquireLock(); // released in Writer!
3762  log_(level, 0, _log);
3763 }

4000  if (m_data->dataType() == PerformanceTrackingData::DataType::Complete)

4004  }

4008  if (!m_data->checkpointId().empty())

4011  }
4012  ss << ELPP_LITERAL(" for block [") << m_data->blockName()->c_str() << ELPP_LITERAL("] : [")
4013  << *m_data->performanceTracker();
4014  if (!ELPP->hasFlag(LoggingFlag::DisablePerformanceTrackingCheckpointComparison) &&
4015  m_data->performanceTracker()->m_hasChecked)
4016  {
4017  ss << ELPP_LITERAL(" ([") << *m_data->formattedTimeTaken() << ELPP_LITERAL("] from ");
4018  if (m_data->performanceTracker()->m_lastCheckpointId.empty())
4019  {
4020  ss << ELPP_LITERAL("last checkpoint");
4021  }
4022  else
4023  {
4024  ss << ELPP_LITERAL("checkpoint '") << m_data->performanceTracker()->m_lastCheckpointId.c_str()
4025  << ELPP_LITERAL("'");
4026  }
4027  ss << ELPP_LITERAL(")]");
4028  }
4029  else
4030  {
4031  ss << ELPP_LITERAL("]");
4032  }
4033  }
4034  el::base::Writer(m_data->performanceTracker()->level(), m_data->file(), m_data->line(), m_data->func())
4035  .construct(1, m_data->loggerId().c_str())
4036  << ss.str();
4037  }
